.TH "tty_driver_lookup_tty" 9 "tty_driver_lookup_tty" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tty_driver_lookup_tty \- find an existing tty, if any
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct tty_struct *" tty_driver_lookup_tty
.BI "(struct tty_driver *driver "  ","
.BI "struct file *file "  ","
.BI "int idx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "driver" 12
the driver for the tty
.IP "file" 12
file object
.IP "idx" 12
the minor number

Return the tty, if found. If not found, return NULL or \fBERR_PTR\fP if the
driver \fBlookup\fP method returns an error.

Locking: tty_mutex must be held. If the tty is found, bump the tty kref.
